  "texts": [
    "Identifying R d with the tangent space T p at p, the exponential mapping provides a convenient way to embed R d into hyperbolic space with origin at p. The exponential map is the most often used function in hyperbolic learning for computer vision, as it allows us to map visual representations from Euclidean to hyperbolic space.",
    "In the hyperboloid model, the exponential mapping coincides with the expression of the geodesic given in (5).",
    "In the Poincaré model the exponential map can be conveniently written in terms of gyrovectorspace addition and is given in (9).",
    "In practice, the exponential and logarithmic mapping functions are tools in vision for mapping representations from Euclidean to hyperbolic space or vice versa.",
    "This is common for example when using hyperbolic embeddings on top of standard encoders or when using pre-trained networks."
  ],
